gomodel:SYNGO_1135  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 5-HT3A receptro subunit characterisation in HEK cells.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P35563] SyNGO ID 1133 (PMID:11876772, EM). Experimental description: The mouse 5-HT3A subunit was tagged with a linker sequence and two bungarotoxin pharmatope-tags on the receptor C-terminus (5-HT3A/BBS) in pCDNA3.1. The human 5-HT3A subunit was tagged with the hemagglutinin (HA) epitope in pCDNA3.1 vector on the N-terminus. Mouse 5-HT3A/BBS and human 5-HT3A subunits were stably expressed in HEK-293 cells by transfection with polyethyl- eneimine (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO, USA) (150 μM per 1 μg DNA) or lipofectamine (Invitrogen) respectively. Cells were incubated for 24-48 h at 37°C in 5% CO2 after transfec- tion to allow for expression, yielding HEK-3A/BBS or HEK-h3A cells respectively." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1135" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

